column16: Rating Total: 106; No Stars: 0 reviews; *: 1 reviews; **: 0 reviews; ***: 2 reviews; ****: 103 reviews;  With Context: 36;  With Image: 27;  With Media: 30;  Local Review: 62;  Oversea Review: 44;

column9:
Best Feature:One of the best in its price class
Performance:Good
Product Quality:Good

[-1 star because the listing says "Ash wood version 4" switches but these are actually the Ash wood version 3 switches.]

There are several reviews on YouTube about this board already so go check those. In summary, it's an incredible gasket-mounted keyboard for the price that's built well and sounds good (see video). The black color surprisingly looks good in person. I've played osu! with it and it's fine both on wireless and wired mode.

However, this listing says that this has the Ash wood version 4 switches when it uses the Ash wood version 3 switches (see pic). Whether that's a good or bad thing entirely depends on the user but the seller should list it properly.

Other than that, the software (which you can find on the manufacturer's website) is unsigned and looks shady but it does work.

My other complaint about the board is the fact that you can't disable the white LED strip beside the Escape key. It's annoying to look at sometimes.

Despite this, it's still an excellent keyboard for its price.
